Package: microsnow
Type: Package
Title: Below or above canopy microclimate modelling with R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ilya", "Maclean", email = "i.m.d.maclean@exeter.ac.uk", role = "cre"),
    person("Vilna", "Tyystj√§rvi", email = "vilna.tyystjarvi@helsinki.fi", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Ilya M. D. Maclean <i.m.d.maclean@exeter.ac.uk>
Description: The functions in the micrownow package contain tools for 
    spatially and temporally modelling snow depth, snow density, snow temperature and 
    air temperatureand relative humidity above snow. Coupled with the microclimf
    package, it includes a complete set of tools for modelling microclimate in any 
    terrestrial environment and is the add-on to microclimf that enables microclimate
    to be modelled in snow environments. 
